---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Card from '../components/ui/Card.astro';
import CardContent from '../components/ui/CardContent.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Kubernetes Security Encyclopedia" description="An encyclopedia of Kubernetes security — terminology, attack patterns, defensive strategies, and tools.">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-zinc-100 mb-4">
        About
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
        An encyclopedia of Kubernetes security — terminology, attack patterns, defensive strategies, and tools.
      </p>
    </div>

    <Card class="mb-8">
      <CardContent class="p-8 md:p-10 lg:p-12">
        <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none 
          prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-gray-900 dark:prose-headings:text-zinc-100
          prose-h2:text-xl prose-h2:mt-8 prose-h2:mb-4 prose-h2:font-semibold
          prose-h3:text-lg prose-h3:mt-6 prose-h3:mb-3 prose-h3:font-semibold
          prose-p:text-gray-700 dark:prose-p:text-zinc-300 prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-p:mb-4 prose-p:text-[0.9375rem]
          prose-ul:list-disc prose-ul:ml-6 prose-ul:space-y-2
          prose-ol:list-decimal prose-ol:ml-6 prose-ol:space-y-2
          prose-li:text-gray-700 dark:prose-li:text-zinc-300 prose-li:leading-relaxed prose-li:text-[0.9375rem]
          prose-strong:text-gray-900 dark:prose-strong:text-zinc-100 prose-strong:font-semibold
          prose-code:text-xs prose-code:bg-gray-100 prose-code:text-gray-900 dark:prose-code:bg-zinc-950 dark:prose-code:text-emerald-400 prose-code:px-1.5 prose-code:py-0.5 prose-code:rounded prose-code:font-mono
          prose-pre:text-xs prose-pre:bg-gray-900 prose-pre:text-gray-100 dark:prose-pre:bg-zinc-950 dark:prose-pre:text-zinc-100 prose-pre:rounded-lg prose-pre:p-4
          prose-blockquote:border-l-4 prose-blockquote:border-gray-300 dark:prose-blockquote:border-zinc-600 prose-blockquote:pl-4 prose-blockquote:italic prose-blockquote:text-gray-600 dark:prose-blockquote:text-zinc-500
          prose-a:text-primary-600 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline hover:prose-a:text-primary-700 dark:hover:prose-a:text-primary-400
          prose-hr:border-gray-200 dark:prose-hr:border-zinc-800">
          <h2>What is This Reference?</h2>
          <p>
            This reference provides a comprehensive collection of Kubernetes security knowledge, organized into focused sections:
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" />
            </svg>
            Glossary
          </h3>
          <p>
            Browse the <a href="/glossary">Glossary</a> for definitions of Kubernetes security terms, concepts, and components. Each entry includes detailed explanations and related terms to help you understand the security landscape.
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary-600 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 6h13M8 12h13M8 18h13M3.75 6.75h.01v.01h-.01V6.75zm0 5.25h.01v.01h-.01V12zm0 4.5h.01v.01h-.01v-.01z" />
            </svg>
            Topics
          </h3>
          <p>
            Reference <a href="/topics">Topics</a> for detailed information on security concepts with impact and mitigation strategies. Topics cover both offensive and defensive security techniques, from fundamental concepts to advanced practices.
          </p>

          <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 7h18M3 12h18M3 17h18" />
            </svg>
            Threat Matrix
          </h3>
          <p>
            Explore the <a href="/techniques">Threat Matrix</a> to view mapped MITRE ATT&amp;CK techniques in phase order and quickly pivot into related Kubernetes topics.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Purpose</h2>
          <p>
            This reference is designed to help security professionals, developers, and DevOps engineers understand Kubernetes security concepts, identify potential vulnerabilities, and implement effective defensive strategies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
